-- 
Ukraine to Hold Tender on Unconventional Gas, Kommersant Reports

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-03-21T08:24:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/ukraine-to-hold-tender-on-unconventional-gas-kommersant-reports.html
  Ukraine  will hold a tender on
product sharing agreements to explore for unconventional natural
gas in the Lviv region and on the border of Kharkiv and Donetsk
areas,  Kommersant-Ukraine  reported, citing Deputy Environment
Minister Mykola Zlochevskyi.  Ukraine has 25.6 trillion cubic meters of unconventional
gas resources in the Donbass area, the newspaper said. About 8
trillion cubic meters in deposits can also be found in other
parts of the country, Kommersant said.  Royal Dutch Shell Plc, Chevron Corp., TNK-BP and Exxon
Mobil Corp. have expressed interest in exploring for
unconventional gas in Ukraine, according to Kommersant.  -- Editors: Jonas Bergman, Stephen Cunningham  To contact the reporters on this story:
